{
  "texts": [
    "To do so, we extended the \"spatial\" vision of our ENN by creating two additional sets of lattices, each encompassing 16 grids measuring 1 km, in a 4 × 4 patch.",
    "Figure 3 further explains the mapping unit structures, wherein in panel (a), we can observe that the 1 km red polygonal lattice created by Kincey et al. (2021) contains 32 × 32 pixels of the underlying terrain characteristics.",
    "The subplot (Fig. 3b) shows how each patch is generated through the green boxes containing 16 inventory grids.",
    "Each box will later be used as the training patches in the ENN, which in turn implies a 128 × 128 pixel structure (32 pixel × 4 = 128) as input data.",
    "The model will then output 16 inventory grids, following the same data structure expressed at the 4 × 4 patch level."
  ]
}